comment.author: 47524421@N08
comment._content: Vickers 422 Warwick B.Mk.I (RAF s/n BV256) converted in early 1942 to C.MK.I G-AGFK, used by BOAC to carry mail, freight and passengers between England and North Africa; their useful load was 9,600 lb (4,354 kg). In August 1944 these aircraft were returned to the RAF and their serials restored.
